== Types == The types of limestone vary according to the water depth of the sea in which they were formed. Because the substrate of the Southwest Islands has repeatedly experienced uplift and subsidence, and due to fluctuations in the sea level, various types of limestone can be observed in different regions and periods.<ref name="R01">{{Cite book|title=沖縄の自然 地形と地質|publisher=Hirugisha|year=1990|author=松田伸也 and Zenko Zemma|language=ja}}</ref> ; Coral Limestone : Limestone rich in fossils of {{ill|Reef-building Coral|ja|造礁サンゴ|12=draft}}. ; Calcareous Algae Nodular Limestone : Limestone abundant in {{ill|Calcareous Algae Nodules|ja|石灰藻球|12=draft}}. ; Cycloperrius Limestone : Limestone containing large numbers of foraminifera such as {{ill|Cycloperrius|ja|サイクロペリウス|12=draft}} and {{ill|Opacirina|ja|オパキュリナ|12=draft}}. ; Clastic Limestone : Limestone containing many fragments of foraminifera, corals, algae, and bryozoans.
